Cubic Spline¶

In [67]:
class CubicSpline:
  def __init__(self, x, y):
    self.n = len(x)
    self.x = x
    self.y = y
    self.h = np.diff(x)
    self.alpha = self.compute_alpha()
    self.l, self.mu, self.z = self.compute_tridiagonal()
    self.d = y[:-1]
    self.c, self.b, self.a = self.compute_coefficients()

  def compute_alpha(self):
        alpha = np.zeros(self.n - 1)
        for i in range(1, self.n - 1):
            alpha[i] = (3/self.h[i])*(self.y[i+1] - self.y[i]) - (3/self.h[i-1])*(self.y[i] - self.y[i-1])
        return alpha

  def compute_tridiagonal(self):
        l = np.ones(self.n)
        mu = np.zeros(self.n - 1)
        z = np.zeros(self.n)
        for i in range(1, self.n - 1):
            l[i] = 2*(self.x[i+1] - self.x[i-1]) - self.h[i-1]*mu[i-1]
            mu[i] = self.h[i]/l[i]
            z[i] = (self.alpha[i] - self.h[i-1]*z[i-1])/l[i]
        return l, mu, z

  def compute_coefficients(self):
        b = np.zeros(self.n - 1)
        c = np.zeros(self.n)
        a = np.zeros(self.n - 1)
        for j in range(self.n - 2, -1, -1):
            c[j] = self.z[j] - self.mu[j]*c[j+1]
            b[j] = (self.y[j+1] - self.y[j])/self.h[j] - self.h[j]*(c[j+1] + 2*c[j])/3
            a[j] = (c[j+1] - c[j])/(3*self.h[j])
        return a, b, c

  def interpolate(self, x_interp):
        i = np.searchsorted(self.x, x_interp) - 1
        i = np.clip(i, 0, self.n - 2)
        dx = x_interp - self.x[i]
        return self.a[i]*dx**3 + self.b[i]*dx**2 + self.c[i]*dx + self.d[i]

Lagrangian Interpolation¶

In [68]:
class LagrangianInterpolation:
    def __init__(self, x, y):
        self.x = x
        self.y = y

    def lagrange_basis(self, i, x_interp):
        basis = 1
        n = len(self.x)
        for j in range(n):
            if i != j:
                basis *= (x_interp - self.x[j]) / (self.x[i] - self.x[j])
        return basis

    def interpolate(self, x_interp):
        total_sum = 0
        n = len(self.x)
        for i in range(n):
            total_sum += self.y[i] * self.lagrange_basis(i, x_interp)
        return total_sum
In [69]:
def segmented_lagrange_interpolation(x_values, y_values, segment_size):
    y_interpolated = []
    for start in range(0, len(x_values), segment_size):
        end = min(start + segment_size, len(x_values))
        segment_x = x_values[start:end]
        segment_y = y_values[start:end]
        lagrange = LagrangianInterpolation(segment_x, segment_y)
        y_segment = np.array([lagrange.interpolate(x) for x in segment_x])
        y_interpolated.extend(y_segment)
    return np.array(y_interpolated)

Comparison between f_prime_x_actual vs f_prime_x_obtained¶

In [74]:
f_prime_actual = np.cos(x_values) - np.sin(x_values)

def cubic_spline_derivative(spline, x_interp):
    i = np.searchsorted(spline.x, x_interp) - 1
    i = np.clip(i, 0, spline.n - 2)
    dx = x_interp - spline.x[i]
    return spline.b[i] + 2 * spline.c[i] * dx + 3 * spline.a[i] * dx**2

f_prime_spline = np.array([cubic_spline_derivative(spline, x) for x in x_values])

f_prime_lagrange = np.gradient(y_lagrange, x_values)

error_spline = np.abs(f_prime_spline - f_prime_actual)
error_lagrange = np.abs(f_prime_lagrange - f_prime_actual)

avg_error_spline = np.mean(error_spline)
avg_error_lagrange = np.mean(error_lagrange)

print(avg_error_spline)
print(avg_error_lagrange)
